overview: "The user initiated a request to significantly improve the aesthetic
  appeal of their sleep questionnaire application. The agent began by conducting
  a thorough review of the existing design, identifying a generic color palette,
  plain backgrounds, and basic form elements. The approach involved a
  multi-faceted overhaul: introducing a calming, sleep-themed color palette
  using OKLCH, redesigning the main form layout with subtle background blurs and
  an enhanced progress indicator, and transforming the welcome screen with a
  hero section and interactive feature cards. All core UI components like
  checkboxes, radio buttons, sliders, and cards were polished for a more modern
  feel. Crucially, consistent styling was applied across all 14 questionnaire
  sections, replacing old gray boxes with themed card-like groupings. The report
  section also received a significant update with consistent gradient headers
  and refined content colors. During the process, a console error related to
  null values in input fields was identified and fixed. The agent also addressed
  user feedback to correct remaining hardcoded alert colors and report section
  gradients, ensuring a fully cohesive and professional aesthetic for the sleep
  health application."
